    "cheatsheetContent": "Work as a formal derivation checker.\nTask:\nDecide whether Equation 1 implies Equation 2.\n\nEquation 1:\n{{ equation1 }}\n\nEquation 2:\n{{ equation2 }}\n\nProof discipline:\n- Treat Equation 1 as the only given assumption.\n- Treat Equation 2 as the exact target to be justified.\n- Do not skip hidden steps or use unstated assumptions.\n- If the target follows, give an explicit derivation.\n- If the target does not follow, give a concrete witness showing separation.\n\nOutput rules:\n- Plain text only.\n- Use exactly the four headings below.\n- Keep the reasoning short and the support section decisive.\n\nRequired output:\nVERDICT: TRUE or FALSE\nREASONING: explain why the target is derivable or why it fails\nPROOF:\nfill this only when VERDICT is TRUE\nCOUNTEREXAMPLE:\nfill this only when VERDICT is FALSE\n\nChecks:\n- `VERDICT:` must be exactly `TRUE` or `FALSE`.\n- `REASONING:` must not be empty.\n- If `VERDICT: TRUE`, `PROOF:` must be non-empty and `COUNTEREXAMPLE:` empty.\n- If `VERDICT: FALSE`, `COUNTEREXAMPLE:` must be non-empty and `PROOF:` empty.",
